UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0883902603001022
KW  - Founding
KW  - Initial resources and decisions
KW  - Temporal stability
KW  - Growth
AB  - Several authors have suggested the founding period as a critical time in the development of a firm, arguing that the resource and decision choices made at this point have a substantive impact on the firm's future. Yet, historically, most studies have measured new venture choices considerably after the founding period. We suggest that the uniqueness of the founding event is important and test its validity through the examination of two implicit assertions. These implicit assertions are those of temporal stability and temporal locus of growth determinants.
